SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1001
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to honor Charlie Becker of Nashville on his
outstanding success in college football
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing a
young man from Tennessee who has achieved great success in college football; and
WHEREAS, Charlie Becker of Nashville helped his Indiana Hoosiers football team reach
the pinnacle of college football by winning the College Football Playoff National Championship
on January 19, 2026, in Miami, Florida; and
WHEREAS, the son of Dave Becker and Tracy Becker, Charlie Becker attended grade
school at St. Matthew Catholic School in Franklin and was a star athlete at Father Ryan High
School, where he won state championships in the 110-meter hurdles, 300-meter hurdles, and
the 4x400-meter relay; and
WHEREAS, on the high school gridiron, Charlie Becker earned TSSAA Division II AAA
West Region Offensive MVP honors as a senior and was named first-team All-Region as both a
junior and a senior; and
WHEREAS, after finishing his high school football career, Charlie Becker, a six-foot-four
wide receiver, was recruited by a number of college programs; he ultimately chose to accept a
scholarship from Indiana University; and
WHEREAS, "Charlie B from Nashville, Tennessee" played primarily on special teams
during his freshman season and at the start of this past season before being called on to play a
bigger role when starting wide receiver Elijah Sarratt went down with an injury in October; and
WHEREAS, taking advantage of the chemistry he had developed with his roommate,
Heisman Trophy-winner Fernando Mendoza, during their extensive summer work outs and
SJR1001
015569
- 1 -

passing drills, Charlie Becker rose to the challenge and quickly became a fan favorite and one
of Indiana's top receivers; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Becker made big catches at key times in several of the Hoosier's
biggest wins down the stretch of their undefeated season, including the game-clinching
reception in the Big Ten Championship against The Ohio State University, as well as four
catches for ninety-nine yards and two touchdowns in Indiana's two College Football Playoff
games before the national championship game; and
WHEREAS, in the championship game, Charlie Becker recorded sixty-five yards,
including a nineteen-yard catch on fourth and five as well as another nineteen-yard catch on
third and seven, to extend scoring drives as Indiana defeated the Miami Hurricanes, 27-21, to
secure the Hoosier's first national football championship; and
WHEREAS, Charlie Becker regularly publicly shares his faith and declared after the Big
Ten Championship, "All glory to God. Without Him, none of this would be possible, so all glory
to Him."; and
WHEREAS, Charlie Becker has distinguished himself as one of the most gifted college
football players in the nation, and he is richly deserving of our approbation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Charlie Becker of Nashville on his many
accomplishments in college football as a wide receiver for the National Champion Indiana
Hoosiers and wish him much continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
